article.headline: Nebraska 46, Colorado 41
article.story: LINCOLN, Neb. -- Ade Dagunduro scored 18 points to lead Nebraska to a 46-41 win over Colorado on Wednesday. Nebraska (16-8, 6-5 Big 12) never trailed and led by as many as eight twice in the game, the latest after Brandon Richardson's free throw made it 38-30 with 6:18 remaining. Colorado (9-16, 1-10) got a three-point play from Cory Higgins, an Austin Dufault basket and another Higgins jumper to cut the Nebraska lead to 39-36 with 4:07 left. But Dagunduro's field goal and a three-point play gave the Huskers a 44-38 lead with 2:25 remaining. Neither team scored another field goal in the game. Nebraska ended the game 16 for 46 from the floor for 35 percent, while Colorado shot 31 percent. Higgins led Colorado with 12 points.
